            "newString": "# OpenCode Provider Support Design\n\n## Overview\n\nAdd support for OpenCode's Zen and Go services as model providers in the CLI through user configuration.\n\n## Background\n\nOpenCode uses a **single API key** for both Zen and Go services. Users obtain the key from opencode.ai/auth.\n\n### API Endpoints\n\n**Zen** (`https://opencode.ai/zen/v1`):\n| Model | Endpoint | AI SDK |\n|-------|----------|--------|\n| GPT-5.x | `/v1/responses` | @ai-sdk/openai |\n| Claude | `/v1/messages` | @ai-sdk/anthropic |\n| Gemini | `/v1/models/{model}` | @ai-sdk/google |\n| MiniMax, GLM, Kimi | `/v1/chat/completions` | @ai-sdk/openai-compatible |\n\n**Go** (`https://opencode.ai/zen/go/v1`):\n| Model | Endpoint | AI SDK |\n|-------|----------|--------|\n| GLM-5, Kimi K2.5 | `/v1/chat/completions` | @ai-sdk/openai-compatible |\n| MiniMax M2.5, M2.7 | `/v1/messages` | @ai-sdk/anthropic |\n\n### Model ID format\n- Zen: `opencode/<model-id>` (e.g., `opencode/gpt-5.3-codex`)\n- Go: `opencode-go/<model-id>` (e.g., `opencode-go/kimi-k2.5`)\n\n## Design\n\n### Challenge\n\nThe CLI uses LangChain, which connects to a single base URL per provider. OpenCode has:\n1. Two different base URLs (zen vs go)\n2. Different endpoint paths for different model families\n\n### Approach: Single provider with configurable base_url\n\nUsers configure in `~/.deepagents/config.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[models.providers.opencode]\napi_key_env = \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"\nbase_url = \"https://opencode.ai/zen/v1\"\nmodels = [\n    # Zen models - OpenAI-compatible\n    \"gpt-5.1-codex\",\n    \"gpt-5.2\",\n    \"glm-5\",\n    \"kimi-k2.5\",\n    \"minimax-m2.5\",\n    # Zen models - Anthropic-compatible  \n    \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    \"claude-haiku-4-5\",\n    # Zen models - Google\n    \"gemini-3.1-pro\",\n    \"gemini-3-flash\",\n]\n```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n```bash\nexport OPENCODE_API_KEY=\"sk-...\"\n```\n\n### Model Selection\n\nUsers select via:\n- Config: `[models] default = \"opencode:gpt-5.1-codex\"`\n- CLI: `--model opencode:kimi-k2.5`\n\n### Limitation\n\nSince we set a single `base_url`, this works for most models. However:\n- **Go models** (like `opencode-go/kimi-k2.5`) would need a different base URL\n- **Workaround**: Users can use Zen equivalents which share many of the same models\n\n### Implementation Requirements\n\n1. Add `\"opencode\": \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"` to `PROVIDER_API_KEY_ENV` in `model_config.py`\n2. Add test assertions in `test_model_config.py`\n3. Document configuration\n\n### Model List (Initial)\n\nOpenAI-compatible (via `/chat/completions`):\n- `gpt-5.1-codex`, `gpt-5.2`, `gpt-5.3-codex`, `gpt-5.4`\n- `glm-5`, `kimi-k2.5`, `minimax-m2.5`\n\nAnthropic-compatible (via `/v1/messages`):\n- `claude-sonnet-4-5`, `claude-sonnet-4-6`, `claude-haiku-4-5`\n\nGoogle (via `/v1/models/{model}`):\n- `gemini-3.1-pro`, `gemini-3-flash`\n\n(Go-specific models like `opencode-go/*` would require separate provider config or future enhancement)",
            "oldString": "# OpenCode Provider Support Design\n\n## Overview\n\nAdd support for OpenCode's Zen and Go services as model providers in the CLI through user configuration.\n\n## Background\n\nOpenCode uses a **single API key** for both Zen and Go services. Users obtain the key from opencode.ai/auth.\n\nServices available:\n- **Zen**: Pay-as-you-go ($20 minimum) — OpenAI-compatible API\n  - Endpoint: `opencode.ai/zen/v1/chat/completions`\n  - Models: GPT-5.1 Codex, GPT-5.2\n- **Go**: Subscription ($5 first month, $10/mo) — two API styles:\n  - OpenAI-compatible: `opencode.ai/zen/go/v1/chat/completions` — GLM-5, Kimi K2.5\n  - Anthropic-compatible: `opencode.ai/zen/go/v1/messages` — MiniMax M2.5, M2.7\n\n## Design\n\n### Configuration\n\nSingle provider with one API key. Users configure in `~/.deepagents/config.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[models.providers.opencode]\napi_key_env = \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"\nmodels = [\n    # Zen models (OpenAI-compatible endpoint)\n    \"gpt-5.1-codex\",\n    \"gpt-5.2\",\n    # Go models - OpenAI-compatible\n    \"glm-5\",\n    \"kimi-k2.5\",\n    # Go models - Anthropic-compatible\n    \"minimax-m2.5\",\n    \"minimax-m2.7\",\n]\n```\n\n### Environment Variables\n\nUsers set:\n```bash\nexport OPENCODE_API_KEY=\"sk-...\"\n```\n\n### Challenge: Different API styles\n\nThe Go service has both OpenAI-compatible and Anthropic-compatible models. Since `base_url` is set at the provider level, we have two options:\n\n**Option A (Simpler):** Use OpenAI-compatible endpoint only\n- Models: gpt-5.1-codex, gpt-5.2, glm-5, kimi-k2.5\n- base_url = `https://opencode.ai/zen/v1`\n- Skip MiniMax models (Anthropic-compatible)\n\n**Option B (More complex):** Use model-specific params for base_url\n- Requires checking if LangChain supports per-model base_url override\n\n**Recommendation: Option A** — Start with OpenAI-compatible models only, which covers both Zen and the OpenAI-style Go models. This is the simpler path and covers most use cases.\n\n### Model Selection\n\nUsers can select models via:\n- Config: `[models] default = \"opencode:gpt-5.1-codex\"`\n- CLI: `--model opencode:kimi-k2.5`\n- Runtime: `/model opencode:kimi-k2.5`\n\n### Implementation Requirements\n\n1. Add `\"opencode\": \"OPENCODE_API_KEY\"` to `PROVIDER_API_KEY_ENV` in `model_config.py`\n2. Update test assertions in `test_model_config.py`\n3. Document usage in CLI help\n\n### Model Lists\n\nInitial OpenAI-compatible models:\n- **Zen**: `gpt-5.1-codex`, `gpt-5.2`\n- **Go**: `glm-5`, `kimi-k2.5`\n\n(MiniMax models require Anthropic-compatible endpoint — deferred for now)"
